@node intro "Introduction"

AminetFTPMail is a program, that let's you get the Aminet Recent
Uploads by FTP-Mail. You select the Aminet Recent mail in YAM, or
let the program scan your folder for recent mails, start AminetFTPMail, 
select the files you want to get in a comfortable list and click the 
start button. AminetFTPMail will write a mail to a ftp-mail site of 
your choise and the only thing you have to do then is sending the mail.

Short info about FTP-Mail:
FTP-Mail is a service, that let's you get files from a ftp site via
mail. You write a mail with the files, that you want to get to a
ftp site, that supports ftp mail and this ftp site will mail the
files that you want to get to you.

This service is excellent for getting aminet uploads, but because writing
the mails with hand is not very comfortable, I have written AminetFTPMail.

@endnode

@node feat "Features" 

Features of AminetFTPMail are:

- TritonGUI
- comfortable config editor
- you can select a predefined FTP-Mail site or specify a own ftp-mail address
- you can choose the max. mailsize
- easy to use
- no limit how much files you want to get (the only exception is the size of
  your email account ;-))
- you have two lists, in the upper you can select which upload you want,
  and in the lower are the uploads, that you want, displayed and can
  be removed everytime. 
- simple but powerful
- the only thing you have to do is selecting which files you want, and
  sending the mail :-)
- you can select one recent mail or let AminetFTPMail scan the whole folder
  for recent mails, you can then get files from more than one recent mail
- PropFonts for the window, fixed width font for the lists
- you can use your own fonts
- you have a status panel that shows you the most important things
- you can choose between getting the .readme files or not
- the DecodeFile tool, that decodes and joins ftp-mails automatically
- there are more, but you have to find out them by yourself :-)
- I DON'T WANT MONEY FROM YOU FOR THIS! (but if you still want to send
  me some money, I won't stop you from doing so ;-))

@endnode

@node req "Requirements"

You will need:

- YAM2
- RexxMast running
- a subscribtion to the "Todays recent aminet uploads" or "Weekly recent 
  aminet uploads" list. If you are not already subscribed then send a mail 
  to "listproc@mail.wustl.edu" and in the body "SUBSCRIBE aminet-daily 
  <your emailaddress>" for the daily list or "SUBSCRIBE aminet-weekly
  <your emailaddress>" for the weekly list. You will then get every day 
  or every week a list with all aminet uploads. Cool, isn't it?
- a minium screensize of 640x400
- rexxreqtools.library  (available on aminet)
- rexxtricks.library (available on aminet)
- tritonrexx.library (included)
- triton.library (available on aminet)
- rexxapp.library (included)

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

Copy the @{b}entire@{ub} directory to a place of your choice.

Run "Install Languages". 

Copy everything from libs/ into your libs: dir.
If you want to make an entry in the YAM/Rexx menu, then there
are some rules:
   - the checkbox "Wait until termination" must not be checked
   - the checkbox "Open console window" must not be checked
   - AminetFTPMail must be called as DOS command.

@{b}Make sure you have triton installed correctly and don't XPK encode
the folder where you have your recent mails stored or it won't work!!!@{ub}

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

When you run AminetFTPMail the first time, or upgrade from an older version, 
then AminetFTPMamil will first open its config editor.

Explaination of the gui:

   Language: Select there your prefered language.

   Pubscreen: Type in the name of a pubscreen, where AminetFTPMail should open
              its windows on.

   Multi Mail: This is a very interesting function, when you check 
               this checkbox you don't need to select the recent mail,
               AminetFTPMail will then scan the actual folder in YAM,
               and you can later choose in the GUI the recent mail.
               So you have multiple mails, you can, for example, 
               collect the mails of some days, start AminetFTPMail,
               and then browse through the mails and select the uploads
               you want to get.

               If you don't want this, don't check the box.
               Then you have to select the recent mail in YAM and
               start AminetFTPMail.
   
   Aminet site: Choose here the aminet site, from where you
                want to get the files. At this time I only know
                two addresses, Aminet Paderborn/Germany and a
                US Aminet site, I don't konw the name, a friend
                told me this address. Select one of the two sites
                or select "-- Other --". If you select other, the
                "FTP-Mail address:" field will be enabled.

   FTP-Mail address: If you have selected "Other" (see above),
                     then you can here specify an email address.
                     AminetFTPMail will send the mails to this
                     address. Please send me aminet sites, that
                     support ftp-mail and are not on the list.

   Max. Mailsize: When you use ftp mail to get files, you must
                  specify a mailsize, if a mail is above these
                  size, the mail is splitted into parts. 
                  You can select between the mailsizes 16kb,
                  32kb, 64kb, 128kb, 256kb and 512kb.

   Get .readme files: When you check this checkbox, AminetFTPMail
                      will get the .readme files of the uploads
                      you want, too. 

   Delete Mail: Check this checkbox, and AminetFTPMail will add the
                DELETE AFTER SEND-Flag of YAM to the ftp mail. This 
                means that the ftp mail will be deleted after it was
                send.

   Uploads list:
   Wishlist:

      Width:   Select here the width of the uploads list/wishlist.

      Height:  Select here the height of the uploads list/wishlist.

               NOTE: The "Wishlist" is the "I would like to get" list
                     in the main gui, but I call it here Wishlist, 
                     because the name in the gui is to long for the 
                     config editor. :-)
 
   Window font:Select there the font that should be used in the windows.

   Lists font: Select here a fixed width font that is used in the lists. 

Click on ok to use the settings or on cancel to forget them.

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

Start YAM.

When you have Multi Mail disabled then select the Aminet Daily or 
weekly mail in yam and start AminetFTPMail. The GUI should open.

When you have Multi Mail enabled, then go to the folder where you
have your recent mails in, and start AminetFTPMail. It will scan your
folder for recent mails and then open the GUI.


Explaination of the menu:

   Write the mail: see "Write the mail" button in the gui

   Register: if you want to register AminetFTPMail, then click
             on this menu point 

   About: display some informations about AminetFTPMail

   Quit: Guess what. ;-)

   Settings: open the config editor

   Snapshot window: snapshot the position and size of the main and 
                    config window.

   Load settings: load settings from a file

   Save settings: save current settings to S:AminetFTPMail.config

   Save settings as: save current settings to a file
   

Explaination of the GUI:

   Mail from: Here are the dates of the recent mails, that were 
              found, displayed. Select a date and the recent mail
              from that day will be displayed in the uploads list.
              You can control this list with the cursor keys.
              
   Uploads: Here are the uploads displayed, click on the uploads
            you want to get. When you click on an upload, it will
            be displayed in the "I would like to get:" list.

   I would like to get: Here are the uploads displayed, that you
                        want to get. Click on an upload to remove
                        it from the list. Beside this list is another
                        list that shows you in how many mails the
                        upload is send to you.

   Address: Here is the address displayed to which email address the
            ftp mail will be sent.

   Max. Mailsize: Here is the maximal mailsize displayed, that you
                  have configured in the config program.

   Mails: Here are the number of mails displayed, that you will receive.

   Write the mail: This button will start writing the ftp mail with 
                   the uploads you want to get. The mail will be quened.

   Cancel: Cancel and quit the program.

@endnode

@node reg "Registration"

At first, I don't want money from you, I just want to know that someone
uses this program. When you are a registered user, I'll mail new versions
of AminetFTPMail to you, and I will answer questions faster.
You have the full version, there are no limits for not registered users.
(I don't want to lock someone out)

If you like it and use it often, please register.

Click in the main gui on the menu point "Register...", the registration
tool will show up.

Fill out the fields, explaination down here, and click on "Register me".
The registration tool will write the registration mail in YAM and you
just have to send it.

The GUI:

(* = not required, if you don't want to tell this to me, leave blank)

   Name: Your name.

   E-Mail: Your email address.

   Street: The street, including number, where you live. (*)

   City: The city you live in. (*)

   Country: The country you live in. (*)

   Your rating: What do you think about AminetFTPMail.
                Range is from 1 to 6. 1 is fantastic, and
                6 is garbage.


   Register me: Writes the register mail to me.

   Cancel: quit.

@{b}Thanks for registering!!!@{ub}

@endnode
 
@node df "DecodeFile"

I have written DecodeFile, because in my opinion it is very uncomfortable to
first save the ftp-mail, then rename it and then decode and join it.

Usage:

Select the received ftp-mail you want to decode in YAM and then start DecodeFile.
If you receive a archive that is splitted into some parts, then select only the
first part, DecodeFile will detect it, when a archive is splitted into parts and
decode and join the archive automatically.
Select then the output path, where the decoded and joined archive should be saved
to.

That's all.

@endnode

@node hist "Histroy"

V1.0 (16-08-1998)
   - first release

V1.0a
   - only two or three people have this version,
     it contained a filelenght recognition routine
   - no official release

V2.0 (17-09-98)
   - status panel added (enhanced)
   - shortcuts for the buttons added
     (sorry, I don't think about such little details)
   - PropFonts added
   - delete after send flag added 
   - Multi Mail added

V2.0a (21-09-98)
   - bug removed, the delete mail button in the config program
     wasn't recognized correctly
   - missed implemation implemented :), I forgot to add the
     font to the triton windows, sorry.
   - added a gui error message, if a error occurs while the
     gui is opened this message will tell you what went wrong.

V2.1 (24-12-98)
   - made it possible to open AminetFTPMail on a pubscreen
   - included the DecodeFile tool for decoding and joining
     ftp-mails 
   - main gui rewritten and made smaller
   - menu added
   - moved config editor into a menu point
   - moved registration tool into a menu point
   - recent mails are marked as read
   - replaced next/last mail buttons by the "Mail from:" list
   - YAM goes into busy status while it scans the folder
   - you can adjust height&width of the lists manually
   - about window added
   - config editor has a new layout
   - you can use now two fonts, a propfont for the window and
     a fixed width font for the lists
   - translated to German 
   - small internal improvements
   - small bugs removed

@endnode

